### NSDataLab API Test Requests
### Use with REST Client extension in VS Code

@baseUrl = http://localhost:5000

### 1. Health Check
GET {{baseUrl}}/health

### 2. Generate Dataset - E-commerce Products
POST {{baseUrl}}/api/generate
Content-Type: application/json

{
  "topic": "E-commerce Products",
  "description": "Sample product catalog for an online store",
  "columns": [
    { "name": "product_name", "datatype": "string" },
    { "name": "price", "datatype": "currency" },
    { "name": "category", "datatype": "string" },
    { "name": "in_stock", "datatype": "boolean" },
    { "name": "rating", "datatype": "float" }
  ],
  "rowCount": 10
}

### 3. Generate Dataset - User Data
POST {{baseUrl}}/api/generate
Content-Type: application/json

{
  "topic": "User Registration Data",
  "description": "Sample user information for a web application",
  "columns": [
    { "name": "full_name", "datatype": "name" },
    { "name": "email", "datatype": "email" },
    { "name": "phone", "datatype": "phone" },
    { "name": "address", "datatype": "address" },
    { "name": "registration_date", "datatype": "date" }
  ],
  "rowCount": 15
}

### 4. Generate Dataset - Sales Data
POST {{baseUrl}}/api/generate
Content-Type: application/json

{
  "topic": "Monthly Sales Data",
  "description": "Sales transactions for Q1 2024",
  "columns": [
    { "name": "transaction_id", "datatype": "string" },
    { "name": "product", "datatype": "string" },
    { "name": "quantity", "datatype": "integer" },
    { "name": "unit_price", "datatype": "currency" },
    { "name": "discount", "datatype": "percentage" },
    { "name": "sale_date", "datatype": "date" }
  ],
  "rowCount": 20
}

### 5. Get All Datasets (Paginated)
GET {{baseUrl}}/api/datasets?page=1&limit=10

### 6. Get All Datasets (Sorted by topic)
GET {{baseUrl}}/api/datasets?page=1&limit=10&sortBy=topic&sortOrder=asc

### 7. Get Single Dataset by ID
# Replace {dataset_id} with actual ID from previous requests
GET {{baseUrl}}/api/datasets/{dataset_id}

### 8. Delete Dataset by ID
# Replace {dataset_id} with actual ID
DELETE {{baseUrl}}/api/datasets/{dataset_id}

### 9. Upload Sample CSV File
# Note: This requires a file upload, use Postman or Thunder Client for this
POST {{baseUrl}}/api/uploadSample
Content-Type: multipart/form-data

# Attach file with field name "file"
